        <h2>What is Veto?</h2> 
        In democratic systems, the Western countries have over time revealed two primary problems: On the one hand a lack of interest in the opinions represented by politicians. Secondly, there is a lack of demonstration of approval or disapproval by the population and a great discontent with one's own opinion is not heard or prejudiced to be. Often it is only the ideas that are spawned by populists of all stripes and "those who shout the loudest," those who are perceived.
        <h2>Why Veto?</h2>
        We aim to present a simply constructed, representative and transparent source of political opinions. The platform will serve to publish opinions to form an opinion and evaluate different opinions both for election campaigns, as well as on an ongoing basis. Veto is to be a leading platform for this purpose and therefore also constitute a tool for opinion analysis.
        <h2>How does Veto work?</h2>
        The concept of <i>Veto</i> based on evaluating only direct quotations from politicians. This will revolutionize the opinion-forming process. Instead of being dependend of the interpretations of the media, citizens can judge its opinion in direct exchange with the politicians.<br>
On veto user can post quotes from politicians with a maximum of 200 characters: Either the politicians themselves, or cited by foreign source is acknowledged. These quotes are then rated on a scale of users with regard to the approval and credibility. Veto thus represents an opinion of the general population.

